The corridor spans Mayfield Road (U.S. Route 322) through the City of Cleveland Heights, Ohio. The western terminus
of the project is Kenilworth Road while the eastern terminus of the project is Warrensville Center Road.
PREVIOUS STUDIES: Have any previous studies (TIS, Planning, etc) relevant to this project been conducted?
PROJECT DESCRIPTION & REASON FOR REQUEST (The reason helps us provide forecasts tailored to the purpose and need.)
This is a signal reconstruction project. All warranted traffic signals along Mayfield Road in the City of Cleveland
Heights, Ohio are proposed to be reconstructed.

Certified Design Traffic - Project involving no new roads* and no new general purpose (GP) lanes.
Certified Design Traffic - Project involves new roads or GP lanes and planning level traffic is complete.
Certified Design Traffic - Project involves new roads or GP lanes and NO planning level traffic is available.
